<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-18T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-18T16:00:00-05:00" n="284" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">362.1163 Watch Tower/15:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at Berlin (<persName type="to">Messersmith</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-18T17:00:00-04:00">May
                                        18, 1933—5 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your May 2, 4 p.m. The Watch Tower Bible and Tract Society greatly
                                appreciated your earlier and successful efforts but now reports that
                                the Governments of Bavaria, Saxony, Thuringia, Lippe, Mecklenburg,
                                Hesse <pb facs="0511" n="407" xml:id="pg_407"/> and Wurttemberg,
                                have officially interdicted its activities and confiscated its
                                property valued at about 750,000 Reichsmarks.</p>
                            <p>Please investigate, extend appropriate assistance, and telegraph
                                results.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>